stylometry: Decision trees are importand in problem solving because they allow you to look at the whole decision making process in sequence. It shows the decisions you could make, the alternatives for each decision, the probabilities of those decisions and the payoffs of the decisions. An example of how a decision tree can be used to solve a problem is if an investor, who has a certain amount of money (lets say $20,000), wants to make a decision whether to invest in option one or option two. With option one, there is a 75% chance that the investor will make $700,000 and a 25% the investor will make $200,000. Option two has a 50% of making $1,000,000 and a 50% of $1,000. By setting up a decsion tree, this investor can look at all of his alternatives, the probablilities and the payoffs all at the same time.
